Projected U.S.-S. Korea joint military drills slammed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 17 (KCNA) -- The central committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League released a statement yesterday, denouncing the large-scale joint military maneuvers the U.S. imperialists are planning to stage together with the South Korean bellicose forces as a more dangerous war provocation against the north than the "Team Spirit" joint military maneuvers and a nuclear test war to impose a nuclear holocaust on the Korean nation.
 The statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Together with the invincible people's army capable of defeating any formidable enemy at a stroke, our young vanguard will not remain a passive onlooker to the present situation where peace in our country is being threatened by the U.S. imperialists and the South Korean warmongers and the tensions  reached an extreme pitch. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The war hawks should not run wild but immediately halt the war rehearsal against the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If they ignite a war of aggression in this land in defiance of our repeated warnings, we youth and students will be eight million human bombs to wipe out the U.S. imperialist aggressors to the last and certainly achieve the cause of national reunification, the cherished desire of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement called upon all the youth and students at home and abroad, together with all other Korean people, to rise up more vigorously in the struggle against the war provocation moves of the U.S. aggressors under the uplifted banner of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration.

Projected U.S.-S. Korea military exercises under fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 17 (KCNA) -- Large-scale joint military exercises to be staged by the U.S. and South Korean war hawks from March 21 are explicitly a replica of the "Team Spirit" joint military exercise and a premeditated war game of higher level for an invasion of the northern half of Korea, which are, in nature, an open military provocation aimed at the DPRK, says Rodong Sinmun today in a commentary.
 The news analyst further says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. warmongers listed the DPRK as a member of the "axis of evil", provoking its dignity, and went the length of unhesitatingly declaring that they would "make a nuclear attack" on it unless their unacceptable brigandish demand is met. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Therefore, nobody can vouch that the soon-to-be-staged war games, which involve unprecedentedly huge forces and latest military equipment, will not go into an actual war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. warmongers should not act rashly. If they and their stooges ignite a war of aggression in this land, we will never miss that opportunity to wipe out the aggressors to the last and realise our cherished desire for national reunification.

Congratulatory message to leader Kim Jong Il 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 17 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il received a congratulatory message from the South Korean youth and students on the occasion of his birthday.
 In the message they extended their heartfelt greetings to him, representing their deep reverence for him on the occasion of his birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 You have developed and enriched the Juche idea with your rare wisdom to formulate it as the great Kimilsungism and indicate a way ahead of humankind, which is your undying feat. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today socialism in the northern half of Korea concluded the "arduous march" and the forced march despite any imperialist moves to isolate and stifle it and registered signal successes in the building of a powerful socialist nation. The credit for this goes to the outstanding leadership ability and army-based policy of Kim Jong Il who has stratagem and pluck of Mt. Paektu, the message stresses, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 You are the great teacher of our nation and the entire humankind and the sun of the 21st century all people look up to and follow. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 You provided our nation with the June 15 South-North Joint Declaration, a milestone for national reunification, in June 2000 to open a new history of the national reunification movement with which to achieve the independent reunification by the united efforts of our nation. As a result, the 70 million fellow countrymen in the south and the north and abroad are advancing along the road of unity and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We, hot-blooded youths in the south, will take the lead in upholding your noble intention in the glorious road to victory and become a human bomb and fortress in the struggle to reunify the country.

Former S. Korean "comfort women" urge apology and compensation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 17 (KCNA) -- Women of South Korea, who had been forced to serve as "comfort women" for the Japanese imperial army during World War 11, held the 500th Wednesday rally in front of the Japanese embassy in Seoul on March 13, demanding the settlement of the "comfort women" issue, the South Korean newspaper Hangyore reported.
 The ralliers expressed curse towards the Japanese embassy, urging an apology, compensation and probe into the truth about the issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also called for the abrogation of "national fund", which is "bonus" donated by nongovernmental organizations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mun Phil Gwi, 77, said that former "comfort women" have demanded an official apology and compensation of the Japanese government and refused to get such "fund" which Japan is persuading them privately to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hwang Kum Ju said: We will continue this rally as long as one of us remains alive.
